                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-310-victim2350 t18270913-310-viclabel1727"></join>, from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>GEORGE RUSSELL. ESQ. On the 11th of July I was in <placeName id="t18270913-310-crimeloc1728">Hyde-street, near Manchester-square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-310-crimeloc1728" type="placeName" value="Hyde-street, near Manchester-square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-310-crimeloc1728" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-310-off1725 t18270913-310-crimeloc1728"></join>, and lost my watch from my fob - I did not see it taken; the two prisoners came up to me in company; and one of them held up some lemons to sell, and at that time I missed my watch and key they were gone in a minute. I looked for it on the ground, but it was not there - Saunders held the lemons up almost close to my eyes - I had seen Lyons with him.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. BARRY. Q. Is your sight not defective, Sir? A. Yes; I missed it directly they were gone; nobody else had come against me - it was in my waistcoat pocket - it was safe a few minutes before - nobody came near me but them. I advertised it as lost, and offered 15l. reward for it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-310-person2351">
                  JOHN 
                  FORRESTER
               <interp inst="t18270913-310-person2351" type="surname" value="FORRESTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-310-person2351" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-310-person2351" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a City officer. I received information of this, and took up Saunders.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-310-person2352">
                  JOSEPH 
                  TAYLOR
               <interp inst="t18270913-310-person2352" type="surname" value="TAYLOR"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-310-person2352" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-310-person2352" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a City officer. I received information, and apprehended Lyons, who I know goes about with lemons and oranges.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-310-person2353">
                  ABRAHAM 
                  COHEN
               <interp inst="t18270913-310-person2353" type="surname" value="COHEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-310-person2353" type="given" value="ABRAHAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-310-person2353" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a confectioner, and live in Petticoat-lane. On the 11th of July, about seven o'clock I saw Lyons give a watch into the hands of Henry Levy; he looked at it, went into his house, and returned with some sovereigns, which he gave into the hands of Saunders - they then all three went into a public-house, at the corner of Arrow-alley, Petticoat-lane. I heard some silver ringing - I went to Taylor's house, but he was out; and at night I saw him and gave him information.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Have you known Taylor long? A. Yes; I knew he was at Aldgate watch-house - I was never locked up there; I have sometimes been out late, and Taylor let me in there; that is not once in a year - I do not go by the name of Tyo; they call my brother so. I work for my brother - I knew the prisoners by sight - I knew nothing of a reward till afterwards; I expect nothing - I do it for the good of my country - Levy lives at No. 1, Petticoat-square.</p>
               <p>SAUNDERS - <rs id="t18270913-310-verdict1729" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270913-310-verdict1729" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 20.</p>
               <p>LYONS - <rs id="t18270913-310-verdict1730" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270913-310-verdict1730" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 16.</p>
